  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Vitamin D deficiency could be a high risk for cardiovascular diseases. It has been recently
      reported that vitamin D deficiency is another cause of heart failure and cardiomyopathies. It
      was found that vitamin D supplementation improved the heart function. The purpose of this
      study is to evaluate patients with idiopathic cardiomyopathies and determine whether vitamin
      D supplementation in cases where there is a deficiency, improves heart functioning.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
